        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n> Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n> \n> It is not clear how this addresses the main issue - that we are using a hard-coded certificate.\n> \n> Is the plan that we would install a self-signed cert as a default, and then override that via a mount in our helm chart with a cert generated by cert-init?\n\nPlease ignore my earlier comment - I misunderstood the Jira.  I thought the issue was that the cert used for SSL was hardcoded, but rather it appears what OOM did not like was including the truststoreONAPall.jks itself in the image.  Thanks!",
